parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure in Wet Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected locking of the brakes while driving in rainy conditions can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes lock up or seize when driving in rainy or wet conditions
the vehicle pulls to one side or loses traction
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft.
